Both reflection and absorption provide great contributions for excellent EMI shielding. However, in consideration of green shielding, less reflection is better. The ideal EMI shielding involves strong absorption with no reflection and transmission, as shown in Fig. 2b. Multiple reflection also plays an important role in EM wave attenuation. Multiple reflections between the front and back of the shield contribute a lower EMI SE. However, when the thickness of the shield close to or larger than the skin depth (δ=πfμoμrσ-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
